{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow drivers on Skilled Worker visas to drive without retaking Driving Tests",
        "additional_details": "We propose that:\r\n\u2022 Skilled workers should be allowed to exchange their valid international driving licences for UK licences without retaking a practical driving test.\r\n\u2022 A full driving test should only be required if a driver has had multiple accidents or traffic violations within their first year in the UK.\r\n \r\nWe think it\u2019s illogical that someone who has been driving for a year becomes incompetent overnight",
        "background": "We want  the UK Government to allow those on skilled worker visas to exchange their international driving licences for UK licences without having to retake driving tests. Currently skilled workers can drive in the UK on their international licence for 12 months before having to take a driving test.",
